HEADWORD: Riptowel
<hw>Rip"tow*el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>r⟦imac⟧p</ets>. harvest + a word of uncertain etymology.]</ety>
<fld>(Feud. Law)</fld> <def>A gratuity given to tenants after they had
reaped their lord's corn.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

